{
  "texts": [
    "We think this may be due to the fact that the Catalan language has different open-source communities like Softcatalà 9 or open-source initiatives like AINA 10 that have been making efforts to produce and share high-quality open data for the revitalization of Catalan on the Internet.",
    "The fact that Catalan is a Romance language and is more similar to higher resourced languages like Spanish or Portuguese may also be an important factor that helps to improve MT results.",
    "Thus, we can conclude that GPT-4 and GT offered similar MT quality results when translating from English into Spanish, Catalan, and Brazilian Portuguese.",
    "The only exception in the languages analysed is when translating into Turkish, where GT clearly obtained better results, and terminology consistency was the only advantage for GPT-4 in this language pair.",
    "Taking these results into account, we suggest using GPT-4 for MT tasks in high-resourced languages (specifically, the above-mentioned languages)."
  ]
}